Class FilterIteration<E,X extends Exception>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloseableIteration<E,X>, Iteration<E,X>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CompatibleBindingSetFilter, DistinctIteration, FilterIterator, IntersectIteration, MinusIteration, OffsetIteration, ReducedIteration, SPARQLMinusIteration

    public abstract class FilterIteration<E,X extends Exception>
extends IterationWrapper<E,X>
    A CloseableIteration that wraps another Iteration, applying a filter on the objects that are returned. Subclasses must implement the accept method to indicate which objects should be returned.
